cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "LogDx-CI: Benchmarking CI Log Reduction Tools for LLM Root-Cause Diagnosis"
message: "If you use this benchmark, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Qin
    given-names: Bowen
    affiliation: "National University of Singapore"
repository-code: "https://github.com/eyuansu62/LogDx"
repository-artifact: "https://huggingface.co/datasets/eyuansu71/logdx-ci"
url: "https://logdx-bench.github.io/"
abstract: >
  LogDx-CI evaluates whether CI log reduction tools preserve enough
  evidence for LLM root-cause diagnosis. The benchmark compares 10+
  log reducers (raw, tail, grep, rtk-{read,log,err-cat}, llm-summary,
  and hybrid routers) on 19 real GitHub Actions failure cases spanning
  eight failure categories and seven ecosystems. Diagnoses from
  three debuggers — Claude Haiku 4.5, Claude Sonnet 4.6, and OpenAI
  gpt-5-mini — are scored against AI-drafted, author-verified ground
  truths using a calibrated formula (diagnosis_score_v1_1) covering
  category accuracy, signal-mention recall, file/test recall, forbidden
  claims, and confident-error rate. The headline finding is that the v2
  corpus produces cross-family-stable AND cross-run-stable benchmark
  rankings (Sonnet/Haiku/gpt-5-mini agree on top-3 ∩ = {hybrid-v2,
  hybrid-v3} on v2), while v1.3 stability is narrower. The release
  includes the full corpus, evaluator code, protocol locks, and three
  release-gate scripts that pin canonical state against shim/config
  drift and provider-error class leakage.
keywords:
  - llm
  - benchmark
  - ci-cd
  - log-analysis
  - log-reduction
  - rtk
  - coding-agents
  - root-cause-analysis
